<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870828-0023 </DOCNO><HL> Rail Unions Plan ProposalTo Buy Southern Pacific</HL><DD> 08/28/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> LABOR SFXTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)TRANSPORTATION, TRUCK AND SHIP LINES, RAILROADS (TRA) </IN><DATELINE> CHICAGO  </DATELINE><TEXT>   A group of railroad unions representing employees of the Southern Pacific Railroad said it plans to submit next month a proposal to buy the railroad.    Santa Fe Southern Pacific Corp., which owns the Southern Pacific, has been ordered by the Interstate Commerce Commission to submit plans to sell the line.    The Railway Labor Executive's Association said it retained Drexel Burnham Lambert Inc. to assist it in obtaining financing for the purchase plan. The union group said it will propose that the railroad's employees acquire the line with the participation of existing management. </TEXT></DOC>